Accumulated Yield specified as mass, not corrected for the reference moisture percentage DDI 184.This Yield Total Mass is the mass that includes the average percentage moisture (DDI 262) if this is measured on e.g. harvesting equipment. This comment is added to clarify and differentiate this DDI from the Yield Total Dry Mass (DDI 183).
Accumulated Distance out of working position
Accumulated Time out of working position

Accumulated Yield specified as dry mass. The definition of dry mass is the mass with a reference moisture specified by DDI 184. The earlier defined DDI 90 is considered to be the total mass that is measured on e.g. harvesting equipment as a mass including a possibly unknown moisture percentage. This DDI 183 is the yield total mass, corrected to a reference moisture.

Accumulated yield specified as seed cotton mass, not corrected for a possibly included lint percantage. This Yield Total Seed Cotton Mass is the total mass of the raw harvested cotton product as it is measured on e.g. harvesting equipment.
Accumulated yield specified as lint cotton mass. This Yield Total Lint Cotton Mass is the total lint cotton mass, after it has been removed from the total seed cotton at a cotton gin.

The total number of pre-cutted product units produced by a device during an operation. Precut Total Count is a total of a device element. It is intended to be used as a task based total value and therefore it is recommended to support the on-time and on-change trigger methods. The total trigger method and the setable property are required for this DDE.

The total number of un-cutted product units produced by a device during an operation. Uncut Total Count is a total of a device element. It is intended to be used as a task based total value and therefore it is recommended to support the on-time and on-change trigger methods. The total trigger method and the setable property are required for this DDE.
